<h2 id="support-reliability">🛟 Support and Reliability</h2>

Platform stability matters more than features when you're mid-season and bookings are flowing. Both platforms maintain reasonable uptime—we've seen minimal outages from either over the past two years.

Checkfront's support operates on tickets primarily, with phone support available at higher tiers. Response times average 12-24 hours for non-urgent issues. Their knowledge base is comprehensive, and most common questions are answered there. For urgent issues, escalation paths exist but require persistence.

Peek Pro emphasizes customer success more aggressively. You'll get a dedicated rep, regular check-ins, and faster response times. This is partially because their business model depends on your success (more bookings = more commission), so the incentives align well. Phone support is more accessible across all tiers.

For multi-location operators managing 10+ sites, support quality compounds. One sluggish support experience at a single location is annoying; the same pattern across an enterprise deployment becomes a serious operational drag.

<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

After years of implementing, troubleshooting, and optimizing both platforms across diverse tour and activity operations, our team's recommendation comes down to scale and business model.